President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Robert L. Sumwalt for the position of Member of the National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB). Sumwalt has been a member of the NTSB since 2006 and served as Vice Chairman from 2006 to 2008. Prior to his role at the NTSB, Sumwalt managed the aviation department for SCANA Corporation and worked as an airline pilot for US Airways for 24 years. He has received awards for his contributions to aviation safety, including the Flight Safety Foundation’s Laura Tabor Barbour Air Safety Award and the Air Line Pilots Association’s Air Safety Award. Sumwalt is also an inductee into the South Carolina Aviation Hall of Fame and holds a B.S. from the University of South Carolina.